Reasoning: The paper proposes a novel online unsupervised learning rule for training the reservoir of a Liquid State Machine, which is a sparsely interconnected recurrent network of spiking neurons. This falls under the domain of neural networks and machine learning, which are covered by several arXiv CS sub-categories. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the most likely category as it specifically deals with neural networks and their applications. cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely categories as they cover a broad range of machine learning techniques. cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as it deals with the control and optimization of complex systems, which is relevant to the training of the reservoir. Finally, cs.NI (Neuroscience and Neuroinformatics) is a possible category as the paper is inspired by the structural plasticity observed in biological neural networks.
